ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: At approximately what time of the day did you first think about the stressor?
How long did the event last?
Notes: 1 = For several minutes; 2 = For up to an hour; 3 = For several hours; 4 = For the rest of the day

ElementDescription: How stressful do you think the average person would find this event?
Notes: 1 = Not at all stressful; 2 = A little stressful; 3 = Somewhat stressful; 4 = Moderately stressful; 5 = Very stressful

ElementDescription: Is the category of the stressor: Housing?
Is the category of the stressor: Money/Possessions?
Is the category of the stressor: Crime/Legal
Is the category of the stressor: Your own health?
Is the category of the stressor: The health/death of a loved one?
Is the category of the stressor: Caregiving for child/children?
Is the category of the stressor: Marital/Partner relationship?
Is the category of the stressor: Other family/Household member relationships?
Is the category of the stressor: Education?
Is the category of the stressor: Work?
Is the category of the stressor: Lack of sleep?
Is the category of the stressor: Other?
Please describe the stressor
How stressful was this situation for you, today, at its peak?
How angry did you feel at the peak of this stressor?
How anxious did you feel at the peak of this stressor?
How sad did you feel, at the peak of this stressor?
How much shame did you feel, at the peak of this stressor?
For how long afterward did your negative emotions last?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = For several minutes afterwards; 3 = For up to an hour afterwards; 4 = For more than an hour; 5 = For the rest of the day

ElementDescription: To what extent did you find yourself thinking about this stressful situation in the rest of your day afterward?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = A lot

ElementDescription: Do you feel that you have control over the stressful situation (not your reaction to it, but the actual situation)?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = A lot

ElementDescription: To what extent do you have the resources (emotional, interpersonal, or cognitive) to deal with this situation?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = A lot

ElementDescription: How demanding is it to deal with this situation?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = A lot

ElementDescription: To what extent do you feel you are able to effectively handle this situation?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = A lot
